Law Seminars International presents the third annual Energy Restructuring
in California conference.  This comprehensive conference provides a unique
opportunity for attendees and speakers to share ideas about the evolving
structure of the market, the nature of regulation in the future and the
prospects for restoring stability to California's troubled energy
marketplace.

When/Where: October 4 and 5, 2001 at the Hotel Monaco in San Francisco

Program Co-chairs: Arthur O'Donnell of California Energy Markets and Edwin
F. Feo of Milbank Tweed Hadley & McCloy LLP.

